postcontent: This is a Excellent Colt Python revolver, .357 Magnum caliber with a 2 1/2" barrel and blued finish.  1976, and for an almost 40+ year old gun it is absolutely pristine, a real, true "Safe Queen". postcontent: FOR SALE: Original Remington M24 in 300 Win Mag – This is a 1998 production M24. This is not a factory refurbished rifle or a clone. I purchased this rifle in 2002 from a SWAT Sniper instructor. This was his personal weapon and was used primarily as a classroom demonstrator. There are NO damages or scuffing anywhere on the gun. Shortly after I purchased the rifle, I used it in a 1000 yard match at Fort Knox, KY. I had never shot a 1000 yard match or even this rifle. I got it slopped in Cosmolene from Century arms, unfired since import. I scrubbed all the metal parts and steamed the stock, although the stock does sweat cosmo slightly on hot days. It was made at the Chongqing Chinese State Arsenal in August of 1954 (receiver marked 1954.8). No numbers match on it, as is typical for these reimports. I did, however, have the headspace checked, and it checks out perfectly in spec. I had a little fun with it and did some "trench-art" markings on the stock. I also put one of those $4 inexpensive trigger kits in it with the small shim and spring, it VASTLY improved the trigger. Additionally, I actually shot and zeroed this thing to exact Point of Aim. It will shoot about a 3-3.5" pattern at 100 yards with standard light ball, and it improves a little with heavy ball. So it's definitely your run of the mill Type 53, but a blast none the less! I should disclose it does have a small hairline crack in the upper handguard, but it really is hardly noticeable when the guard is on the rifle.

Anyways, I'm most looking to trade for something different. I could take cash, but I think a trade would be preferred. Let's start at maybe $250 trade value or $230 cash. I would like to trade for an M.95-30 Steyr mostly, maybe some odd 7mm Mausers, Antiques, I'm open to anything. PM me with offers, and I can send more detailed pics at that time. Located in Temecula. Thanks for looking!

postcontent:
For sale here is my Smith & Wesson Model 60-15 “Pro Series” .357 magnum revolver that I had custom made by the S&W Performance Center.   This one sports the slab-side 3-inch barrel and tritium night sight.  This is a private sale from an ordinary hunter and shooter.  I am not a dealer or collector.  The gun is in 100% perfect condition and has only been fired around 50 times.  I’m only selling it to fund a deer rifle project.

See all the high-resolution pictures here at this photo-sharing site …… 

https://model60pro.smugmug.com/Smith-and-Wesson-60-Pro-Series/ 

This is truly the slickest S&W J-frame you will ever handle.  The barrel-to-cylinder gap is almost imperceptible and paper thin.   The double action trigger pull is smooth and light and in single action the hammer falls with the slightest press.   The cylinder locks up rock solid with no shake whatsoever.  

It is very accurate and sighted in to hit with 158 grain .357 magnum loads.  With .357 loads the point of impact “sits” right on top of the front sight.  Light .38 special 158 grain loads hit right behind the Trijicon tritium night sight dot and are also very, very accurate.

The gun weighs only 23 oz unloaded and would make a great concealed carry revolver, or sidearm for a hunter or outdoorsman.  With the included holster it sits tight on your hip and you don’t even realize it’s there.

INCLUDED as a whole package with the gun are: the original case and all the literature, keys and factory-fired case, an additional soft zipper case, an additional hard-side case, three new speedloaders, three belt pouches for the speedloaders, and over 400 rounds of factory ammunition (a blend of heavy .357 loads, mild .357 loads, and premium .38 special defense loads.)

The price is $800 cash, and the sale is for gun and all the accessories as one lot.   (Sorry, but I don’t wish to sell any of it individually.)

The sale will be 100% documented with the usual common-sense precautions taken.  I will need to see and keep a copy an original Nebraska Driver’s license PLUS either a current Nebraska purchase permit or a current Nebraska concealed carry permit.
